4/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWv3qgz0W7lCdLW6lZ3mZW4sxDpd1tmzL8N8RNDPBGp-ksVZcNpH1T9fHBW1WHRyF3bQxRHVxmN2T97TGMbW903MwJ6M4rwXW3TjSxp1pkRCVW2vdg3w8h9HH-W8HRm813Mn04jVl4Xj992GN0kVxfTBt86wNqXW88GSQc6dMqGhN5BvVTQDqwLYN7ys7r6yXc19W7-b-sM52V3NYW75mrFB6k5gbsW8l9ndG4YrvlVW9kyzFV5FYyx4W1Yg0Dw5YGzXPW25BPVw4TQc8KW8lPdS68G_NTkW7FzzHT6GtKxFW7_lmLx6cYQc8VP_j5312YLnLf31bRdM04\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#00a4bd\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"hgAQx2nE\">\r\n        <img alt=\"The Batch top banner - April 24, 2026\" src=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/hs-fs/hubfs/The%20Batch%20top%20banners%20(86).png?width=1200&amp;upscale=true&amp;name=The%20Batch%20top%20banners%20(86).png\" style=\"outline:none; text-decoration:none; border:none; max-width:100%; font-size:16px\" width=\"600\" align=\"middle\" class=\"stretch-on-mobile\">\r\n        </a>\r\n      </td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </tbody>\r\n</table></div>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old1\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old1_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"rich_text\"><div style=\"line-height:125%; text-align:center\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Georgia, serif;\"><a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3lYM-W6N1vHY6lZ3lYW8mDnbK2RPWhnW8JSCR55P7zD6W1vmJv-5fdX_qW2Ypbhh2n9ZpZW41BGLM6rF7rZW4tdDPh5jfxMzW2DZr-W6b5myrW3Wg7Q71LhzQ3W4CQWn-1Np03KW517v801xpkVhW3l1CVt18dwQ7W4BWyWT6LRPFMN8C9nPpNyMYcW66MkYt4gcRK9W2c2xKw8k27TQV1KnGj2W1GBhW4DDFPX5Vpw4yW8_nRXp11fdB0W6Gb1L22tP-hXW4tcHLf5V5R6bN8Vl2mlPWBTgW3Lh15d8_kPy1f2cxWsC04\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size:15px; font-style:initial; color:#f53b0d; text-decoration:underline\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"Y5q3J6B/\">Subscribe</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:thebatch@deeplearning.ai?subject=RE%3A%20Tips%20and%20News\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size:15px; font-style:initial; color:#f53b0d; text-decoration:underline\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"dpgz9vS1\">Submit a tip</a></span></div>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia, serif;\">Dear friends,</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia, serif;\">Coding agents are accelerating different types of software work to different degrees. When we architect teams, understanding these distinctions helps us to have realistic expectations. Listing functions from most accelerated to least, my order is: frontend development, backend, infrastructure, and research.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia, serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Frontend development</span> — say, building a web page to serve descriptions of products for an ecommerce site — is dramatically sped up because coding agents are fluent in popular frontend languages like TypeScript and JavaScript and frameworks like React and Angular. Additionally, by examining what they have built by operating a web browser, coding agents are now very good at closing the loop and iterating on their own implementations. Granted, LLMs today are still weak at visual design, but given a design (or if a polished design isn’t important), the implementation is fast!</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia, serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Backend development</span> — say, building APIs to respond to queries requesting product data — is harder. It takes more work by human developers to steer modern models to think through corner cases that might lead to subtle bugs or security flaws. Further, a backend bug can lead to non-intuitive downstream effects like a corrupted database that occasionally returns incorrect results, which can be harder to debug than a typical frontend bug. Finally, although database migrations can be easier with coding agents, they’re still hard and need to be handled carefully to prevent data loss. While backend development is much faster with coding agents, they accelerate it less, and skilled developers still design and implement far better backends than inexperienced ones who use coding agents.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia, serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Infrastructure</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">.</span> Agents are even less effective in tasks like scaling an ecommerce site to 10K active uses while maintaining 99.99% reliability. LLMs' knowledge is still relatively limited with respect to infrastructure and the complex tradeoffs good engineers must make, so I rarely trust them for critical infra decisions. Building good infrastructure often requires a period of testing and experimentation, and coding agents can help with that, but ultimately that’s a significant bottleneck where fast AI coding does not help much. Lastly, finding infrastructure bugs — say, a subtle network misconfiguration — can be incredibly difficult and requires deep engineering expertise. Thus, I’ve found that coding agents accelerate critical infrastructure even less than backend development.</span></p></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old2\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><table class=\"hse-image-wrapper\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n  <tbody>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color:#3b3b3b; word-break:break-word; text-align:center; padding:10px 0px; font-size:0px\">\r\n        <img alt=\"The illustration shows a racing dynamic with labeled cars, highlighting various software development stages.\" src=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/hs-fs/hubfs/RACECARS-6_1200px.jpg?width=1200&amp;upscale=true&amp;name=RACECARS-6_1200px.jpg\" style=\"outline:none; text-decoration:none; max-width:100%; font-size:16px\" width=\"600\" align=\"middle\" class=\"stretch-on-mobile\">\r\n      </td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </tbody>\r\n</table></div>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old3\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old3_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"rich_text\"><p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia, serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Research</span>. Coding agents accelerate research work even less. Research involves thinking through new ideas, formulating hypotheses, running experiments, interpreting them to potentially modify the hypotheses, and iterating until we reach conclusions. Coding agents can speed up the pace at which we can write research code. (I also use coding agents to help me orchestrate and keep track of experiments, which makes it easier for a single researcher to manage more experiments.) But there is a lot of work in research other than coding, and today’s agents help with research only marginally.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia, serif;\">Categorizing software work into frontend, backend, infra, and research is an extreme simplification, but having a simple mental model for how much different tasks have sped up has been useful for how I organize software teams. For example, I now ask front-end teams to implement products dramatically faster than a year ago, but my expectations for research teams have not shifted nearly as much.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia, serif;\">I am fascinated by how to organize software teams to use coding agents to achieve speed, and will keep sharing my findings in future letters.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia, serif;\">Keep building!</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia, serif;\">Andrew&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size:18px; line-height:1.5\">&nbsp;</p></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_16890053646291\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_16890053646291_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"rich_text\"><h2 style=\"margin:0; font-size:21px; line-height:150%\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">A MESSAGE FROM</span> <span style=\"color: #000000;\"><a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3kwW2JlDBP6pVKhFW13B0-v4Wzb7WW2zg2f43jPZtdW1hS-cf1DSgHJW5-Wxbg4497PSW6lmYTS5BQBhjW7DphcY4Dc2zwN2NR3fxQPvVVW5Rynzz6g6LrFW3MXHqC9df0QhW5YK6j08x2WZrW4Rdq1d2khXxfW3S7h-r4zS0GDMRQ72Ss6JHVW58CXPg4yPtwpVn1z9z3cV6t7W8hG93x715XGXW4sJtKT5hQXYTW15VcZs53stNrW5rzQRC4lN57DW8KN69S3QdzflW5CkVrV9j2QwKf4SF-mT04\" style=\"font-weight:bold; text-decoration:none; color:#000000\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"5QsDfwQ9\" target=\"_blank\">DEEPLEARNING.AI</a></span></h2></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_16848647586863\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><table class=\"hse-image-wrapper\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n  <tbody>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color:#3b3b3b; word-break:break-word; text-align:center; padding:5px 0px 10px; font-size:0px\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDX43qgz0W8wLKSR6lZ3pVW4ZHTww3DlYW3N7mKLXydc4YJW8G70FD2mwRF-W6Nj0rX36-DW0W5ZyW108-xlhwW30DvHg44CKj5N3kQzPM-xZk0W5Sd99V2m6_bFW3QMyXt8DDHHRW3ZKg9Q2KFskTW1CNrS97J7gwrW7QnsJ88Gtc7lN25T1hlQpLb-W6TvR301CR3NRW43CPLN8cfK7BW4BJN-47FlYvVW2Pj8qq4FhLgkN5H65gjcxHXpN3KhL2r5_pTdW9jkCb15Tkrh9W4nT_Gd1BYg33N5QvjB4-d2tCN31RX4rdqV8bW81gzVJ5Lkh2YW1vQ_dV84XRpZW4hfLZx7wHWKDVzl0VB4pbb4-W5Qx7m-1PpK6cf5YlmZF04\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#00a4bd\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"j2SSuKGJ\">\r\n        <img alt=\"Promo banner for: “Building Multimodal Data Pipelines”\" src=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/hs-fs/hubfs/The%20Batch%20ads%20and%20exclusive%20banners%20-%202026-04-17T163922.597.png?width=1200&amp;upscale=true&amp;name=The%20Batch%20ads%20and%20exclusive%20banners%20-%202026-04-17T163922.597.png\" style=\"outline:none; text-decoration:none; border:none; max-width:100%; font-size:16px\" width=\"600\" align=\"middle\" class=\"stretch-on-mobile\">\r\n        </a>\r\n      </td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </tbody>\r\n</table></div>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old19\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old19_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"rich_text\"><p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit;\">In “Building Multimodal Data Pipelines,” you’ll learn how to build pipelines that handle images, audio, and video from end to end. You’ll turn unstructured data into something you can query. <a  href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDX43qgz0W8wLKSR6lZ3kXW1l0-LS1XM-GLW4NVlrQ3Tj0h1W2jsLdW5nYYq0W35Z50h2XkHMcW8q1zM57dPNp5VV1bKG8gqss5W47KBP_1xnFh-W7b00Zj1FhrDsW6Ps_md5TSRqyV7VYmS5sz9TvW8-znYZ80PfDVVRhhcv3_X4Y2W8Wn6S58SFbdSW1xpk-f2nBPT3VNs50P4m8-SzW7W9l7z2LFhySW15J6hY98fZwzW3hz9fG8VsGKGW3B5pyM5sf095W60L0Hx4_DWgcW15rsq185Dr9pW7fCZ345D45thVjmX7z6qJ0PcW7ckJx-1FCStkVJFZcR5gll6xW4d84tt24yGXNW92gvvc6bbqt9W3_3QvN4dSyJrf7KY--804\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"1\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"r2gkKEsX\" target=\"_blank\">Enroll for free</a></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old7\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old7_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"rich_text\"><h1 style=\"margin:0; font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size:32px; line-height:125%\">News</h1></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_16195246841011\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><table class=\"hse-image-wrapper\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n  <tbody>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color:#3b3b3b; word-break:break-word; text-align:center; padding:5px 0px 10px; font-size:0px\">\r\n        <img alt=\"GLM-5.1 excels in SWE-Bench Pro and Terminal-Bench 2.0, leading in coding and reasoning tests.\" src=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/hs-fs/hubfs/GLM5.1.png?width=1200&amp;upscale=true&amp;name=GLM5.1.png\" style=\"outline:none; text-decoration:none; max-width:100%; font-size:16px\" width=\"600\" align=\"middle\" class=\"stretch-on-mobile\">\r\n      </td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </tbody>\r\n</table></div>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old12\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old12_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"rich_text\"><h1 style=\"margin:0; font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height:125%; font-size:32px; font-weight:bold\">GLM 5.1 Aims for Long-Running Tasks</h1>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">Z.ai updated its flagship open-weights large language model to work autonomously on single tasks for up to eight hours.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">What’s new:</span> <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3mxW9lJ5wD2myh6qW6Xvjdt7lNfmpW44QJfN3_N5ZnW8YLngn2KBZsDW1sr1zM3jZ_kGW7YvXct1_DGCSW7QnKWj7fxdMjW5WX0nJ5WgKyyW4pHMlB1YP411W2T4MKb3pDcnWW9bjc1t8CCjNmW5xV99987yfKXW5XMdnF8syz8mW91lXx37LvjvkW2zn_C_559hY_W5W9SpN8804y2W8Lgz4k44QKd9N5KpVgDPyKFpW47GBRR9dGw55VQY5vQ3wS8DhW5SmCg48GH17SW3BCLHG1ftFMHf5Dmpml04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"d2HYmzGE\" target=\"_blank\">GLM-5.1</a> is designed for coding and agentic tasks. Z.ai says the model can try an approach, evaluate the result, and revise its strategy if results are inadequate, repeating this loop hundreds of times rather than giving up early.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"line-height:150%\">\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><strong>Input/output:</strong> Text in (up to 200,000 tokens), text out (up to 128,000 tokens)</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><strong>Architecture:</strong> Mixture-of-experts transformer, 754 billion parameters total, 40 billion parameters active per token</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><strong>Features:</strong> Reasoning, function calling, structured output</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><strong>Performance:</strong> Highest-scoring open-weights model on Artificial Analysis Intelligence Index, third on Arena Code leaderboard, led SWE-Bench Pro (in Z.ai’s tests)</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Availability/price:</span> Weights available via <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWv3qgz0W7lCdLW6lZ3lKW2RbscT56JcK-W44f9376_1sxRW2w06cB5p99VRN4MG6v9_72sDW8354bk8z0-KLN1h6_hy9WLhBW56Rz2Y69y8PyW9jm7pg7Vz0bXW7S9LZT1t1PvpW1xnQmH1V_y9vW7t4PQ_43XzMSM4JXpJx8ZK3W8ggX_j8y3xSTW4bSVCz3dX37NW148wJ_67jMrMW4_dmRB6MLLg9F8K46sx5fJsW3dP_Jr17nTpgW3RFQbj5Hy-0BW4fz7Nf50pCwqLK15QDZVwdW1cthn24_h7qpW3k9Qfb40ldMhW7BXbty6Sb06df64dWpY04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"Xllkx0pJ\" target=\"_blank\">HuggingFace</a> for commercial and noncommercial use under MIT license, <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWv3qgz0W7lCdLW6lZ3lPVjQbV23T97gNW4kg39655sT3_W8TgD548-tFj_N94w7pyYGwmGVW_H4T5MmWN8W3Mw0Cd8FkXB9W5Hjny_6-X3P0W2F4F5r7T4y-TW34mLF24-GJJsW6gLxCH5_LtjJW4x5cz23gWsPnW1w5yqx8NWr6sW7tJNxn1BJJR0N6YhZpH3Q2rxW5cvhlD3HFkkgW6RmY7X4TDpJDW9lGHpD7PTGjQW33phjB3CQh-nW3qBF0v5v2WGWW7Vhy4q4l7pfRW22N-VQ88qwqFW7JMDn478NTd2W6rBBLQ7Wdk05N5jh9qgbgzPTf96j_9K04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"IgTRx9/P\" target=\"_blank\">API</a> $1.40/$0.26/$4.40 per million input/cached/output tokens, coding plans $48.60 to $432 per quarter</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><strong>Undisclosed:</strong> Specific architecture, training data and methods.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How it works:</span> Z.ai has not published a technical report specific to GLM-5.1, which appears to follow <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVj5nR3bW50kH_H6lZ3nqW1HYDxr7K_GcWW4H8YJl5_sSDcN2wwXv2Jf-SDW6_-hbG2_LkYtW3xTq0L8VLBVRW2Dbfsw5KLrKvW7S0CdH7psGTBVJ83Zr4hCLlgVgcB6j6qHyDMW4K_Hzc51hkbXW1GRWHF1gw8f_W4xdcLy3mtF-yW9gqbQ-8TMTD6W769dDf3v-4Q-W417WZ84bPMDDW7mGzJb48Cl0lW4R8YqL18tdbJW8y0J9n8n1VMHW8CZmCM2R7clfW4sN36_7-NSZ1W1Rv_w02PKCSHW7Pk3GH84Jb0KN3k7ChGxV5SWW4FVHKj46LJ4CN5mWD5Q_kLYZW2nr6j01zxwt8W1JLDzJ1583k4VmdmmP1Xbpk1W3vTBXG47Kf95W1_mV-h5wSsM2W8gcLL519Xh0vW8-Mz_T4p7Z4kf7c4m4d04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"GH7y7CwH\" target=\"_blank\">GLM-5</a>’s basic architecture, attention mechanism, pretraining, and input/output size limits. The key improvement is sustained productivity in long-running tasks.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"line-height:150%\">\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">The company said it <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWv3qgz0W7lCdLW6lZ3m5N1F1wlZHR8RRW5vk1r26PN9GvW5bRz3P8vRtzVW82PF6V73NhjlW2bXB323B-rqzMhP1D-Z6XQHW9cpQCh4jPqDrW7_HCSH5GKz9wW11ZS-l4KlR6YVRY2vS6nzr1ZN88qWvRncKqPW3-BmPk99mHf2W4Bq9cF5psjBLW5j6g6T1wgdNZW9grKMH2jMSk1W1wy6tj8HK8lqW2y-TJb1DGXZMW8jnsYd993xwXW77SB6v6w_LHhW4jLz5T6vdCcFN4nZkXTs-_LjVXNLGs557M1cW7ynysG6nCdGbW806lj732mJsVf1M50Bz04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"vH6yGdHd\" target=\"_blank\">optimized</a> GLM-5.1 for agentic coding but did not specify how.</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Where GLM-5 and many other models produce final output within a certain token budget or until they determine that further reasoning won’t change the results, GLM-5.1 cycles through planning, execution, evaluation of intermediate results, and evaluation of its approach until it judges the task to be complete. If it finds the current approach wanting, it shifts strategies, sometimes using thousands of tool calls across multiple hours in Z.ai’s tests.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Performance:</span> GLM-5.1 achieved strong coding results among open-weights models but trailed proprietary models in tests of reasoning and math.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"line-height:150%\">\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">On Artificial Analysis’ Intelligence Index, a composite of 10 tests of economically useful tasks, GLM-5.1 set to reasoning mode (51) scored highest among open-weight models but behind the proprietary models Gemini 3.1 Pro Preview set to reasoning and GPT-5.4 set to xhigh reasoning (tied at 57) as well as Claude Opus 4.6 set to max reasoning (53).</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">On <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3mgW4CmKwG4TL_z_W6C_y_c2jWdBCW3v_p1h7cb1FQW57rMvK8zqG5fVR_g5n3rKNRGW7xfTqg8GzpQ0Vzxm1j7cCnhSW5Nl9BX3Z9m6LW5YdC3f7y1g8nW6bhB9f6PWsXwW8ZmWlJ1FNDp1W7YybmC264FdmW6HDvSC26_mMjW6-Vf7M1W_T8JN2W5yBFS3M_7N2pf4hMZw1znVp91d15bKv3tW3_c52K8H0hg8W8ZhXMY5t6zW-W1jSQbY7XyPZBW1ySZ7t5SzhCXW5sNlZD81_wbVf1sd_yT04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"OoW9nTty\" target=\"_blank\">Arena’s</a> Code leaderboard, which ranks models based on blind head-to-head comparisons, GLM-5.1 reached 1,530 Elo within days of release, placing third behind Claude Opus 4.6 (1,542 Elo) and Claude Opus 4.6 set to reasoning (1,548 Elo).</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">In Z.ai’s own tests, GLM-5.1 <a   href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWv3qgz0W7lCdLW6lZ3pqW5xr6y58jhkPYW7q0zBL8PY-HkW69zr677h4cLYVL60Yc2J3kyWW4HfZLQ2b_qQVW1tJyHD27TDQWW1lqnPM4bFnJhW7RX6cH75kgtPW5KJ4mh8_lhyyW5vTKMN1qX8CbW1kX7dz8FNlDXVl2KqL2-SpJSW3qt-jp5z6JV9W47ZY3D2B0CcsW27vljF3smMXRW1hxN6v97Rp3tN6X8gZPPtHjNW4jLH1Y5g7P-XVkc7v88kRXlmW30MDWK6dLrhcW74HBw_4gzl3DW95mWT63bHTYyW2Kn1RC3bhcQGW7Kb-n48x2BtDf3ds8C004\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"1\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"2oervqh9\" target=\"_blank\">led</a> on SWE-Bench Pro, a test of real-world software engineering problems drawn from GitHub, achieving 58.4 percent compared to GPT-5.4 (57.7 percent), Claude Opus 4.6 (57.3 percent), and Gemini 3.1 Pro (54.2 percent).</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">On CyberGym, which tests cybersecurity reasoning, GLM-5.1 (68.7) <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3nMW25tQ1W3b5vWMW18Lj536K84nZW93H2rW5L7y6xW6mKcgm7x_CgsW6S7GrL2GtcGKW2jBth42tW2Z9VzSL6n6hplDVW8K9s1611nddNVq-0NK6s0nZMW8nlb3S2gTRH7W8cly7c3-XpvlVRtCk8188jHXW4gpzFv7t9zQyW97K8lH827807W4HXRBB2G3YR_N6SVsG3yrknxVRh1pk3ZpL4-W2n6D713xxCpKW207sHR1-GxXkW5Yhw_n42Gb5KN79dLjzr3FpwW5VRTDY658wWrf3scv_204\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"1\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"W/pfgbyJ\" target=\"_blank\">achieved</a> the highest among models tested by Z.ai — prior to the advent of <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVj5nR3bW50kH_H6lZ3pLV3fDxH4bBnYqN8YzTtSxrTVHVCj7t-8K4mlcW1KFTrW5zcnYRW984HxV7XWqN9Vr73sS1F90K5W4rT7ty2n98GJW7LbxH72bG8HVW8sz-C3625f5NW1tp7Rc4HMvSgW2M19VK8v8QX7W7pjRcK7tsFZPT6QZ-3rGn5kW8lFx5Q3M6xMFW77jkgq80GsD4W3TbTB2708H9HW3m10q070Q_CFW1TFnlp2TfQnpN924QR3k__X4W8xMf4R7XJ-15W4tgqCQ576p9QW7Stm0K1znnVzW1HxTVL8wlrKxW26WDPD45jjL8W6tcF0866zBF5W8dFDmW7qx71CV-6Nc-554cJdW99LvrK7v_n0yW8B4WRZ5CZ7mTW3MW_8X1xh5SVW5kQ-7H4CM-TnW17JWFl88XQ0df4VXwtK04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"D604y3uA\" target=\"_blank\">Claude Mythos</a> (83.1 as reported by Anthropic) —&nbsp;including Claude Opus 4.6 (66.6) and GPT-5.4 (66.3). Gemini 3.1 Pro and GPT-5.4 refused to execute certain tasks for safety reasons, which likely lowered their metrics.</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">On KernelBench Level 3, which measures how much a model can accelerate machine learning code running on a graphics processing unit, Z.ai measured GLM-5.1 (3.6x) behind Claude Opus 4.6 (4.2x).</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">GLM-5.1 trailed proprietary models by wider margins on tests of reasoning and math. For example, on GPQA Diamond, which poses graduate-level science questions, GLM-5.1 (86.2 percent accuracy) underperformed Gemini 3.1 Pro (94.3 percent accuracy). On AIME 2026, competition math problems, GLM-5.1 (95.3 percent) fell behind GPT-5.4 (98.7 percent).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Price increase:</span> <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVW3qgz0W69sMD-6lZ3kPN7yn57YJpjFTW5FTYVN1G5cx4W8Z72Fs68L_H5W3Rl92K1ggWTNN4k79HJ4KSTyW758CNj7RpSvlW1Fbf878RHLVkW9kz2W76hnqqkW5W7bhn2WrKgcW187ZNW53R7s2W3yz9_T4w4flVW6_KrQY4YJZZNVCNdmm7684gCVv8rX_7prGPDN5r4LW5XfyppW21DFns54kWTvW2txFYV7gv0dRW73k6D43mN3yQW5JjbcX7FqF87W18hjxp3YDFm_f5hnTX204\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"tKNLUh86\" target=\"_blank\">Z.ai</a> priced GLM-5.1 significantly higher than its predecessor. Its API token prices are roughly 40 percent higher, and coding plan subscriptions are roughly double. Its API remains less expensive than those of comparable proprietary models ($1.40 per million input tokens versus $5 per million for Claude Opus 4.6), but the gap is narrowing.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Why it matters:</span> The ability to work autonomously for hours rather than minutes is a growing area of LLM competition. The lengths of tasks completed autonomously by AI agents have doubled roughly every seven months, <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDX43qgz0W8wLKSR6lZ3mYW6gkblG1b_w3rW1GqWpm2drnr4W9dyyXG5BLWDtN7PY8JnLbzD0W7c5c9_6tZFWTW2JzMzP4ZJrcSN4W_zGjjpCNdW7JJL8Q6NzkjXV_tj7B3C7D8sW4ZmM4f6ThDnHW27PNwv25QnMkVcNnMH4_y_5KW5hpbBX2-4w4bW1vztby8BFRW3W7RqnJ27mY2xcW2lWjmG6M-cLgW7F7Q1Z4gV0sCVGFGDb7Z8RLMW7x2KQG2RgZFkW6wjc7C2JFm6zW4BlW-x3NtMYDW5qrMV329yDFxVXRkqJ46_X98W3F97T91tgRg7VMTlMt119z9mW8hq8-s74cGH5W2bLQkr7b96sRN52J9ZykNJw5f5C_ttz04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"Oes2yB3I\" target=\"_blank\">according to</a> METR, an independent testing organization, and Anysphere’s Cursor integrated development environment <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDXn3qgz0W95jsWP6lZ3lTW6hvjhK3KBRTrW6twH6h4knHqYM5XQFfqv44cW2pHtFW2QHJ4zW91z8-Y5FB3mVW4t8N7c6cyWDKN61wQrN4ZtbVW4J4cQq6MlVLxW99ff8r362vYcN7D2YR9-q_0LN3F6N3n92m0-W4C8FD_67pFYZW6c50bK4ltbQcW59JYvg6lrdszW2kxsq52KzpZ0W2TS_-d2NMglZW8q9KPm409j78W3CYMqN1tKqzcW3QkHhD7FX43hW9dtMBW5m6WvcW2jzlW31rzBgwW1yFl4f66gkTgW4W9Kf814mrMyW97cXhZ65p9qBVVHbDR4FZ5WnW78nW981ZRqCHVSttgr8kGPwXW1Jsmh76S_nZQW6cV1nV3z2mFLW6tlr7P31JltNf6rv5lC04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"R7P0Ljq3\" target=\"_blank\">ran</a> a swam of agents for a week. However,&nbsp;benchmarks that are designed to test sustained performance, such as <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3pPVhHDm03rPCc_W50GH7R5CdQ_8W3YmZpk7fWY1NW6whzrQ5DltGKM3cTl1SqqwdVGJXPg4t5JNtW3DTM6L44z1gLW1HQwSv31LHytW6STDM83_7ZV-W2Yq2YX4T836jW2s79-67SZFVYW8f3Yfz1r0x-SW54ZYxw1sDLFCW70syVF1N-sWLVcTxHR1f7j6YVL3t0832v8H5W8H0z8n7SGmMfW8Vy9KP5DRvWrW3lQ-6x3krpNvW4fTj-57VV18hW99nPXV2C9rSrV8Cxl08-w5sSf5D-5QP04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"YM839YAN\" target=\"_blank\">SWE-EVO</a>, show that even top models successfully complete around 25 percent on long-running coding tasks.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">We’re thinking:</span> If GLM-5.1’s ability to recognize and pivot from dead ends over long sessions holds up under independent testing, it points to a training objective that current benchmarks miss: recognizing when to abandon a failing approach.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p></div></div>\r\n  <table role=\"presentation\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"100%\" class=\"\" style=\"\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size:18px; color:#3b3b3b; word-break:break-word; padding:0px 0px 10px\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_17370396178185\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><table role=\"none\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"vertical-align:top\" width=\"100%\">\r\n  <tbody><tr>\r\n    <td align=\"center\" style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color:#3b3b3b; font-size:0; word-break:break-word\">\r\n      <p style=\"font-size:1px;border-top:1px solid #000000;width:100%;margin:0 auto;\"></p>\r\n      <!--[if mso]>\r\n        <table role=\"none\" align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:1px;border-top:1px solid #000000;width:600px;\">\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"height:0;line-height:0\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n      <![endif]-->\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</tbody></table></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_17241662452411\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><table class=\"hse-image-wrapper\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n  <tbody>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color:#3b3b3b; word-break:break-word; text-align:center; padding:5px 0px 10px; font-size:0px\">\r\n        <img alt=\"A humanoid robot with teal and white elements handles metal parts in bins on a factory floor.\" src=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/hs-fs/hubfs/HUMANOIDS.png?width=1200&amp;upscale=true&amp;name=HUMANOIDS.png\" style=\"outline:none; text-decoration:none; max-width:100%; font-size:16px\" width=\"600\" align=\"middle\" class=\"stretch-on-mobile\">\r\n      </td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </tbody>\r\n</table></div>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old9\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old9_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"rich_text\"><h1 style=\"margin:0; font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height:125%; font-size:32px; font-weight:bold\">Humanoid Robots Work Factory Floors</h1>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">A small number of humanoid robots have made their way into industrial settings, where they’re roughly matching the cost of human labor and propelling some workers into higher-level roles.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">What’s new:</span> Agility Robotics, based in Oregon, is supplying humanoid robots to Schaeffler, a German maker of automotive parts in the first operational deployments of humanoid robots, <em>The Wall Street Journal</em> <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDX43qgz0W8wLKSR6lZ3mhW3nhPm-2kfGQBW2pnXcr92wjPkVVzQH-3TfNVVW4tlCy54ynczlW8HxKyK30LW00W1GPcXz9kVq1pVJ51kq2cbjDLW67NX728vJD5KW2mkT5W4QXWhXW2gxHL72TdqNmW2fZT064B60sXW8vfLvP4Sfx2PW1-KFGD7B25PzW2TQZfl63D0_6W46l-vL2mh-78N2M7t5R3dZPCW3s__5p3Y_zrzW6gnQMY4NQNC5W7RkZJ416GggZW97JX_73dHq4zW6mdDMq8lQB8FW4TJSSW261sbSW4y6D7093WMK7W7229M18g4csgW1J9TDJ4C8q_3W93NNgk83YlzlN4B1Cv4S46htW7gnmWy8_tl8Wdx7j_P04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"K5D01P/Y\" target=\"_blank\">reported</a>. Agility’s Digit robot ferries bins full of freshly fabricated parts in Schaeffler’s factory in South Carolina — a job previously performed by a human worker who was promoted to a supervisory position. Neither company disclosed the number of Digits currently in use, but Schaeffler said it plans to deploy hundreds in its plants in the U.S. and Europe by 2030.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How it works:</span> At the Schaeffler factory, <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3nBW4h2b5H2X5Pf1W2f8DlR32Zt9fW3fzWRY63Qv5cW27dnw_1ryHG_W6Xj9lJ3zt35NW6Q8bpg8RhWwkW37tNvV2Qt2BKW4TYFDl4y_f3XW1BwfjJ8lZ8QYW4djtq68gYv1WW8bKb3g47k4fsW17RMnw4FxHkXF5R6B1yyd-3W1D1dsj74CklMW1L1ScQ2zcr4cW5FJ4nz5P8g-3W8x6HRk8wm1nwW4PHj6y1YKJZBW5h6xc05Kn05gW4M2nvz6vncg6W64BpMR8M2qllW4q4XPF1_vDrVf2yTMzR04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"dICiiIcZ\" target=\"_blank\">Digit</a> carries 25-pound baskets from a stamping press to a conveyor belt, a traverse that takes about 1 minute to complete. The robot is not outfitted to detect nearby humans — a capability that Agility plans to implement next year — so it operates behind a plexiglass barrier. It works for two four-hour shifts with a break in between to recharge. The company has revealed few <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVC5nR3bW5BWr2F6lZ3lyW1pjznP5V0b3NW4vY0B125fYdpW18bw8M8KgRmTW3Qh0Qc3kYdLcW1D7LqP2ZdbpDW1l6_3H47T3hnW4b1Zj659NMxkW46Gnp95xzD24W8kLrDg9lCd0XN7ZjsSBlzb-WW6DDGNM7VtKVkW6t8c4Z8j9l7CW5pksR93tWqt8W4_HnKC7R5mfKW1K9gY78F95sGW522y907cCs5_W4pV5HD3W7xJdW4mpGRR5V3z8YW1pF9nx26TD47W95Zm_55j2GNBN6g2Q9wHN-yQVmM3GT18MDqNW6jbbJ059nT08W7M13LN61l381W5mFc3629j9fdW91Yv871Wt-Q3W14pkM85bppSSW4FhX7j4CPF7yW2nhdBV7zHSPQW1jxcbK2sXW0LVD6kWV5TzSHkW7TLQpz860XCtVyr9jy5ZM9qxMfXGmVsVMHDf5Fjsy204\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"Uhu51Pxo\" target=\"_blank\">details</a> about its technology including its processing hardware and AI models, datasets, or training methods.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"line-height:150%\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">Digit is built to human scale (5’ 9”, 143 pounds) and has legs with inverted knees for lifting; arms designed for lifting parcels and maintaining balance; four-fingered grippers; a torso that houses processing, batteries, and sensors; and LED&nbsp;“eyes” that it directs toward its current focus. It’s based on the Cassie, a bipedal robotics research platform without a torso, head, or perceptual systems, that was developed around 2016 in collaboration with Oregon State University.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">The robot’s sensors can include RGB depth cameras, LiDAR, a motion-sensing inertial measurement unit (IMU), and unspecified encoders that measure the position and velocity of its joints.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">Walking control is dynamic to manage uneven terrain, recover from disturbances, and climb stairs and inclines.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">Agility engineers map work environments ahead of deployment and configure specific tasks on-site. Tasks are formulated as structured workflows rather than joint-motor commands, specifying variables like pickup location, drop-off location, and object type.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">Agility did not disclose Digits’ price but said each robot costs $10 to $25 per hour, while an entry-level job at the Schaeffler factory pays $20 per hour.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Behind the news:</span> Currently, real-world industrial use of humanoid robots is limited to a small number of early, narrow deployments in warehouses and factories, where they assist with specific, well-defined tasks. Most other humanoid systems in industry remain in pilot or trial phases. All told, around 200 humanoids are working in factories today, according to a McKinsey consultant who told <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">The Wall Street Journal</span> he expected that number to grow to 5 million by 2040 without incurring substantial reductions in the manufacturing workforce. Generally, <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3nFW164Ymc1J-lj6W8SKJ_y245Wl_VHPhMp81vVDqVRlyMF8rPZMsW3XvCHy4w9NbmW39gZ5p6DzmFgW6FWdBM45LdKmW8fD8Yv84mz7-W4cxPbB2CKTjKW4bHgDn8qzgJLW1_mXXW2t3cFxW98WfYC9gPP87W54tpdT4p8wwCW2wvzWg6Rg1m-W57KSsq99RkFPVGld3x8QzSCDW22b_xw2_2GPrW3n6VN26RXq5fW2VMnlF5RmTfwW1z99156rPdpHW6yj6P73mW2yPW8c1KqL6BzjMcd6l9Xq04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"FT6Fv2Hk\" target=\"_blank\">research</a>&nbsp;suggests that robots displace humans in specific tasks, driving a restructuring of jobs and upgrading of the remaining roles. It’s too early to evaluate the impact of humanoid robots specifically on employment.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Why it matters:</span> Humanoid robots have become widely <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDXn3qgz0W95jsWP6lZ3lVN2N-L9BQMJ3-N4Z-Qp5kvqGDW5X71LQ24J51kW4C9yYF48ZXJFN135SL2_rXRlW4CNhvH2mDkHlW99nYK91y6yWrW89s9b88ss66RW61tHZY8KspKvW8fq6mC292BFZW20VhXs6zK6rZW3zj02s2VsGvJW5l2gWh2bv6ScN31WgDW5P3xVW8V1cc_8LV3htVPdx9L1H0mzdW1ZHdVL1jS1VKW64THG929k9_9W5QMW5-6G45q7N23MYGtkYdYKV1s5rW1R-5VKTbn4-8Gc-HxW7Gg8M87G0392W1gJnh_6VgqyqW65nvMX1Wdqw6N3y-hFsNQV0KW8HcC1H7jnG5dW46-zCv5SwXW1W1pd3tX51mZj9W6V0KTF6NzzXTf1xz21l04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"Kwf4bl0c\" target=\"_blank\">available</a> only in the past few years, thanks to improvements in batteries, motors, and AI. Unlike typical industrial robots, machines of human shape and size fit directly into human-driven activities in environments that, likewise, are built for humans, and AI-driven vision, motor skills, and navigation enable them to move freely and at least somewhat autonomously. Schaeffler’s use of Digits in South Carolina — a step beyond pilot programs such as tests of Agility robots at <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDXn3qgz0W95jsWP6lZ3nLW2jydhL8Ssy3pW5-FcqL8mwcHrW5ZJ_wW4lYsVcV2bNVd8RJpxrW7GDm3M654SFJW7wTCcd7pBX9zW2WJCKn33jG60N7q5-yR9LTv3W2FKTFV79zqtpN9gg0-QpksgrW559Mh47dYfkCW5_3Qj28TlMtPW5nysPk1NR95mW7fbJYN18GnNPW4YQC1z4DS6s_W5vXGYq2HBgRcN2bbYsfjM4TSW7GptHw3-kDbvW4n4VZM8h7xRPW30vD6_4PTbdYW2D3cmf3_K40ZW1JWV6Q43HKSbW468fBx5X2M7fN7XDYmyY2nNKN6lsGnxt1lzvW98rFMY8xRyJmW8fzCb68_9cdLW7CyT1c6Zpq6FW6KfP5z4Mv2GcW2crP2-6tPzKSf8KPg_b04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"BTOQGfH9\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a> and <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVC5nR3bW5BWr2F6lZ3mYW4K7YB_82gwlqW5B_J9W4KlRl9W4BlS5D3kvRt-V176Qs8KjXQrW6Nn3Kj3l6w4vW3mcYxd1lxsy_W79YVtx5-s7GLVK7N7V4fflChW2gLsMm7s7xJZW3yD7w5499NmKVQnzQx6QDMjVN4Gjq4RtZY_4W3-_xVN32MYxSW4tfK4M6lfjzwW5n1GvS4XsCHCW8DqLcr7NpqGMW44vwmC7LMBXDW7CDBdL3HxY9JW4LvyKj4vzyDnW4nShjF5HCjRDW1fF2Hs4j6PQnW235Mxt79VrTWVJ36wk1Xd1_yW7y6lhf4Sj2yDW1Wl2hF87b-BMW1Cdf842yFYcLW8BQcj372127NW8wm0866jr-9ZN1bmNFN_fxHTW7FVlBg7hL-X5W51bgq266N27SW8TMk_33bBJZ7W8jPfGR6rwtKbW4-qhhH763c-Zf8-gfcb04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"H4w5zPJI\" target=\"_blank\">GXO Logistics</a> and BMW’s <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVW5nR3bW6