Q7_g9BPW3MY3TH3R_xdSW7mvxcx3_xGNxW2h_10S6L8BKTW9lSKsV2WDMdLW5Z5sgV1jx7Y9W9ldbns1rM3TGW18lhRN11_Tm2f8jtBMx04\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-hs-link-id=\"1\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"H71JU3BH\" style=\"color:#237b94\">Subscribe today</a>!</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p></div></div>\r\n  <table role=\"presentation\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"100%\" class=\"\" style=\"\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size:18px; color:#3b3b3b; word-break:break-word; padding:0px 0px 10px\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_17370394853571\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><table role=\"none\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"vertical-align:top\" width=\"100%\">\r\n  <tbody><tr>\r\n    <td align=\"center\" style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color:#3b3b3b; font-size:0; word-break:break-word\">\r\n      <p style=\"font-size:1px;border-top:1px solid #000000;width:100%;margin:0 auto;\"></p>\r\n      <!--[if mso]>\r\n        <table role=\"none\" align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:1px;border-top:1px solid #000000;width:600px;\">\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"height:0;line-height:0\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n      <![endif]-->\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</tbody></table></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_17370394878062\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><table class=\"hse-image-wrapper\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n  <tbody>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color:#3b3b3b; word-break:break-word; text-align:center; padding:5px 0px 10px; font-size:0px\">\r\n        <img alt=\"Aerial view of a large data center with a red prohibition sign overlayed, indicating opposition.\" src=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/hs-fs/hubfs/DATACENTERREVOLT.png?width=1200&amp;upscale=true&amp;name=DATACENTERREVOLT.png\" style=\"outline:none; text-decoration:none; max-width:100%; font-size:16px\" width=\"600\" align=\"middle\" class=\"stretch-on-mobile\">\r\n      </td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </tbody>\r\n</table></div>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_17768779500402\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_17768779500402_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"rich_text\"><h1 style=\"margin:0; font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height:125%; font-size:32px; font-weight:bold\">Anti-Data-Center Revolt Gains Traction</h1>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">Resistance to new data centers is mounting across the United States.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">What’s new:</span> Opponents of data centers are registering their disapproval through legislative channels and, in two recent instances, through acts of violence. Objections to these facilities include their impact on electricity prices, consumption of electricity and water, noise pollution, proximity to residential neighborhoods, and sprawling size. Around $64 billion worth of data-center projects have been blocked or delayed amid local opposition between May 2024 and March 2025, one research group <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWv3qgz0W7lCdLW6lZ3lsF7zTdGMytvzW6nLBTp88dgc1N592cwhZFzY7W6ytHdv2v_7-WN5JZlctKRXqzW25jY2n2j2dPPW1k2JD91H72NTW5qVkGT54d_6qW7mSSyt91Ws-XW1ccXLG7H7BfSW6Jgf-s3-qbN8W21GdMd8yNp2YW3kBgl36kf9g2W96ssVB9kn1lSW7YjC6z7ftk8XW3JrlxW9d-46kW7V0LQq719dLVN1j41SBlmqqMW14-px93ShS4PT9DJP1qzGfPN6NhTMN5rnrWW34f9vM7sc8mmW1jPwpH3g2jCmW5p0PKq3bc36_f1yNVpT04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"5WzNE8VU\" target=\"_blank\">estimates</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How it works:</span> Some of this resistance is being expressed through democratic channels.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul style=\"line-height:150%\">\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Maine’s state legislature <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVC5nR3bW5BWr2F6lZ3n5W1vhVjn3cTvGCW70wFFB8yMG_jW2_5cXF7HbTr_W4-qdb97dzxKyW3_81xy7p-l2FV53svN2SLfl5W3_YDcC2wz4f9VNcJK43S_mnqN4Vzk8SVyXMVW52Kgrg6gDf7vW1ZnjV85h9SrjW4d6j5p4Kmsq0W3T-dP68Phmz1W6wjCpj4Z9sCvW8vb3cN5MKGBlW1ygm-Y7gvTHfW8tLr-M8pqClqVxQb4n8k41qZW4H5Scy9kF0k4W2dmzXw5C4ZC7W6--N_63VdH_tW30WX0w42CX_sVrCWHq8KcCKqW3Xm16X2M1clYW6xYfF_1q2zP5W44SZ_P2Gtzq4W4Sp8_C2g6FCfN7Rn40MJpnHzW7bXfQ76LfJxLW5FQDdW1zvxS6W96VHbH7V4c5JW2HXRPY2Z04pGV3rv6z7xjXLtN6BLX2S9678Sf6DMzK-04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"wNohy8y/\" target=\"_blank\">passed</a> a bill that places a moratorium on new data centers that require 20 megawatts of power or more until 2027. The measure awaits the governor’s signature. It&nbsp;would also establish a council to study the impact of data centers on the electrical grid and on electricity prices. If it goes into effect, it&nbsp;will&nbsp;become the first statewide ban, and others may follow. At least <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDX43qgz0W8wLKSR6lZ3mDW2zWr8c6cpD0zW8Hby-d3J0vwbW1yMmc14Q92QhW30TPyr1fQZSlW35d9c239kRNxW8XzJFg4D1RZxW1JGpC84-r48fW1K3NXR82ZHTMN15vMcCk6RK0N6XTj-PLf6J2W6TwV1-6wtFqtW4VSWd24YN0bGN1FvLj8bgSv1W6FjVSl2K2RNjW73JSbG15ScKWN71jf-rc9z6MW1PGlh38k8p7hW3Hwp-z1j5MrgW2rDc-N4TCXhmN2Tqg0TkzqcsW15dbhW3VCQK8W661H_g17bg2RF4-KNXNQDfDW62lQrv2kwJ9tW8WTSKX7cQhFCN72XKcPRgVmZW5YDyrv69F6gMW8_NJDk2rDQR6f82mhsR04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"Qf6Sbn61\" target=\"_blank\">12</a>&nbsp;other states have filed data center moratorium bills in 2026.</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">The city of Port Washington, Wisconsin, recently passed a referendum that requires voter approval before it can grant tax incentives for large projects including data centers. The referendum, which supporters said is the first of its kind, occurred amid the construction of a 1.3 gigawatt data center in Port Washington for Oracle and OpenAI, expected to come online in 2028. City leaders offered tax incentives to attract the project.The referendum passed on a two-to-one margin but is under legal review after business groups challenged it in court, <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Politico</span> <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVj5nR3bW50kH_H6lZ3pNW1P3K7D5DpjyYW2Nt6Hm62gZnLW5mCyJ43l5xl4W2JcV4S9gVpfNW8D67h34tzQn1W3bQDz_8WyMXhV_xL-n526t87W3QKcJf4zT9R_N5s1G4pJ0qC7N5LPFdGx5YstW39jVwz3LzJMLW4RfyrF1L3LhSW3fxBGv7cJrsXN1m9R0rL5KLpW5ZbcwF3JZC4rW7vg8sj7-tlPNVydW9L2WCDjpW7mxplx2K8rw-W4CDgCN59TF_FW19wvcX7dNK3jW7_yw761Qqy0dW5_7LT-1C6Rs3W8JNqXs67l-3dW3wfbY26QdnJKW673dtD61bSxPW3nTBPj3SsRY5W13rvTQ6WQjxpW8J6-p949FdCQW8-Qw_Y3FBslCW9cYbyM7fHjNFVhZKSn8_Fhq6W1zpYQ85XfSrXf1r246R04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"gQJLGNzs\" target=\"_blank\">reported</a>.</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">In Festus, Missouri, voters <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVj5nR3bW50kH_H6lZ3p2W3G4Vn427xR8bW80Kl4y5dVtcWN5Hg03VqfWNMW4fD6Jw73XJYkW3Xnq2M62ZBlGVWJ0wj2z0-nlN6nbsL11F9ZvW8hjgLL2mzV3fW4sCN4v4HxkrSW2T0l-x29LYgLW5Txs275qLnW-W4qZ1tH1x_29WW1WRmdV6f4_4lW8-Jw3Y5YmSd2W8Ch6Jp9frdyLW5tdqvc59vNzvW4nWnSv67bT0bN55JgJFpXXRjW3S2fcg95sssvW7H4z_28B-n4rW6PpcDq8Rv4sNW8JDYY15S31XgW7x2Jyv6tX6VCW7cbgMx41zsbkW1jZvM03fwfRTW5PJ7kD1n5FMKW4fp4cd3f8LmJW2n0rHy2SQFxrW5JS68Q4hNxhJW8fPd927CtnJnVlwKpr9ddctXN1XwXGyMj5zPf7HMFgH04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"Z6SOE3NZ\" target=\"_blank\">ousted</a>&nbsp;all city council members who had voted to approve a $6 billion data center in the city.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">A citizen-initiated <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVW5nR3bW69t95C6lZ3mXW7cv4vX7qsDP4W98XJz18X1qhZW7dv4yr8BG0QnW4khgRy8Cl8HvW33lcyL8dFFDbW54Q0906Ns0gHVBWxMm1dfvWtW6tyCXZ1VQ7zbW35r9Fv2YyWpbW66rk_D98zltqW5Dx7cv1qqQxHW2gL36-4lqssVW3LwbXH4FdHvRW6Gr8Ks5pvYV8W79Z6p18yzdljW7Zsmys8STnSbW8tBMx29bm8f9W2JMYvP3_vr_pW5k4Hn61Xc4WBW8SXwzd1Wfgm2W50KMck8M9gFqW19tP2g4v9X-jW4lsvLz2YctKhW7lz6Sz7lFyTsW4lbB5D8Y34nZN1PnvxqFf3pfW18_-6d88BP07W8R3d2l28hPj-W71ZQB979lxL8W1V4hNG8Qj84NW76ZJ7Q7sR-MBW1-JT9y6pqYvKW12qYsm7VwzLvV2KCc02ztjbbW6svLnl7V19XyVzLbw22b6-QLf4XYf3b04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"rVUzzBlO\" target=\"_blank\">ballot measure</a> in Ohio aims to amend the state constitution to prohibit future data centers that require over 25 megawatts. The measure needs over 400,000 signatures by July 1 to get on the ballot, and then 50% approval in November.</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Boulder City, Nevada, <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVj5nR3bW50kH_H6lZ3nkW3HwRXY4bZ6bFN2nYpJjPRBbHW3Sd7lh8b9FljW2_sMYH8lJswxW3F5lrf2sPgcvW6Rxh0C2JPxbwW3bPChY7Ys3G5W28NDFc1lnt9XN1sTn76BRlS-W2sDmnF2kR960W10HwXH8RN-BsW8dlM8V4SlmZdW1D8FtG1SGcrTW4Jv49h1B5BjcVPrb-K7RQjfQMZpYCdqykBSVF_NB97GfBgZW52Tjwt1GyhJtW4FnyBB6vYdF1W5nFc-R89k8dVVdtgMZ7zHVw_W3YbTys8pwF7yN91jVJXLjxrpW4Fc6Z24blfXVW3qXSZX2zxjh-W22TDBt2sNVZwN787_Bkx9sQsN6l5x2KSMnMpW40x7lg1PLlbKW1J3_F811Qq3hW3nqfcK5yWyn8W2lSrxD1h6Qj3f4_GDVv04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"UPeMoY2+\" target=\"_blank\">postponed</a> a scheduled hearing for an 88.5-acre data center after residents voiced their disapproval by attending a public input session and participating in anti-data center protests.</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Opposition has also surfaced in <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDX43qgz0W8wLKSR6lZ3pGW6_936X2_lmBGW3lxwmQ61m-6CW7RQLzJ1rZ6TXW1rs-521DMdFzV9Q4ks7gHnDrW3qjjVv5_4WrRW3jNnT33MChhJN2lW3pMDbQ_BW5wW-PQ5B-PyPW1tvly06MhpCGMvR89xjby_jW77xv_z4tmmvZW7rwDJ01-0rtpW5x35RR4133KwVvcQmg61dJ3yW772G1m4qWWl5W64Hw567CsNcWW7Fwdq-7J-q3zF1TyM63pfjrW3szY5z5065fZW2sdJ0k4JY0CqW8X-X4m1H2SHNW2lmxSl55g_qhW7Z_cXl4475HlW94vVyD3k_RYlW8dQRkD2dyYrwW9kmqbY5VQPXzW8cqQlH595JTBf2QC_4404\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"zjAchFxo\" target=\"_blank\">Maryland</a>, where residents in two counties rallied against proposed data-center developments.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Violent responses:</span> Antipathy toward data centers has been implicated in violence in at least two cases.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul style=\"line-height:150%\">\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">In San Francisco, a man recently threw a molotov cocktail at the home of OpenAI CEO Sam Altman. Less than an hour later, the man went to the OpenAI headquarters and threatened to burn down the building, <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">NPR</span> <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDX43qgz0W8wLKSR6lZ3lpW2qHzvG3zj7XKW1dS45B2yrKHYW94LBtR69TRSCW4_bjW07ZxSrXW2Rt83f12WnpxW3D471X97Zc78W5XvVrC2njs-8W1CLkr37yZZWnW3skG5_7dGVkTVlLhg56yjzWdW4yD4q33VvVmbN8M8jXj3xLTmW8llF8C21G9-LW3pJ3zc6DkSGWW96YtmH15bFX9W85RWbR5Cw0BpN50BK9-q-wmgN62LBw7kwdVLVzGH7Y11xDhZW58zntZ4r5m1dW41-pZ19hk-N4W2DdlSf1lgXn5W4XfWMw4hD4-wN7w06174tBrPW1gt0SN3q7tJBW2xrD8d31Dl0dW1t9pGN3qHlZCN8ZQr-xzJLbjf4GMJ0x04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"w76Q0e39\" target=\"_blank\">reported</a>. The man has written about the risk that AI poses to humanity, a federal affidavit <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWv3qgz0W7lCdLW6lZ3psW5kdPMq2zCGrwW128bL_1CSRdHW5q3Jxg809S-kW8Nj8nq3bSSQ5W8_Fy1m9gwQm4W7dXbbx3YdtCMW4MVYKc5spb5SW8vK98P4GVFZFN4PD4G4-l0ckW3XjD5G1qHSlzMH9t8zD6jsBW8gq2CF1wCCp5W1Mrn7K3SFt4DW2r2F1D7hFVY9W515_tc7KM_bRW5VFWkR1ztbtBW3bhZ1R4vqNyPW6y18T47Bfhh1W1GJW1k8Gz673W5N_MM22Gz1N1W9f-sRk2Bg42tW9bH77f4SyPgkW5wR-vn4pW_qKW7gW3vy54h0dYf6_-ssC04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"R+G6jwEG\" target=\"_blank\">states</a>.</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">13 gunshots were <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDX43qgz0W8wLKSR6lZ3nZW1bd8rg2PJpvQW7qsVPc4pWvg7W7n1V2y6YxjBrW4Tn-hW8Hx5HHVvMrF_5_7d1FW13HH3h3cX8KfW5KTKgL1359vBW1Kqgg73V92y7W4_DBn55RZcmtW9kPGl88GDh8MW28pJKH10tBqSW44H7TF5_90mNW8Jp5fY15T7HKW71tYXy4LpLj2W3xQHMv7mTgpGVCLZ0G3Q3cG8Vy-1Mf3ssmJgW2LrpQs3ryl-KW2FNbZ81f_1QqN4QQ1s1Xq2ghW242ppC83bZ4hV_hz1G14PxspW9l0y-k23BwgMN8_fSkr6CydNW7PrtJb1XxYHtW3xKcCH5s8hdtW23cYBX2HkdBDW3-7Y5h90656Kf6Zk-SP04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"1xwI6R0c\" target=\"_blank\">fired</a>&nbsp;at the home of an Indianapolis councilor, who had supported a $500 million data center in the city. A note that read “no data centers” was tucked under Gibson’s doormat.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Behind the news:</span> Lack of transparency around some of the projects is a key gripe of opponents. In the Missouri development, for example, the operator of the data center has not been publicly identified. Critics also point to the environmental footprint of the facilities, particularly their noise levels, large square footage, energy demands, and water consumption. However, newer data centers have more environmentally friendly designs, such as more water-efficient closed-loop systems to cool their servers. Further, an increasing number of data centers supply their own power through <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVj5nR3bW50kH_H6lZ3nVW86zDR-4qqDxFW4zsxyJ1N_z2sW6cTy-z8Z83HYW4kpCf94nVBpzW3yJwd812g4K-W5rZ25v22V534W7cNdpJ1P5hDrW7Jw4Xc1Q73JRW8BrwBj8swd8zW5hsMC05CyLLlN1qfCdK3T105W4byyPT5Q611nN7H5-MWtGnNsW6kfD_W4Y5VyyW907vSB8MsfndW9lVn6c180YBFW1QJDxp3BTt4VW7BKDHv6SvNx-W2mqHt47BdLXlW7gMH_32gmBjzW5XxYQ74zt8VfW4P0pLH1-X1-zW84g1xM3PznRKW4zT69b2ymZSjW5_6gl42Vj62pN4q4-TkW6GW-W7x-sSj5JvSDbW5P-PP95tQ2grN7kt3f6TMsl7W33Zfk641YVZrW3PgnBn2-H302W1fRlfJ91Lk7zf5vJcd-04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"kf39eGmD\" target=\"_blank\">privately owned, off-the-grid power plants</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Why it matters:</span> The rapid growth of AI has led to surging demand for data centers, but electricity is emerging as a key constraint in some regions. Tech companies are racing to build new power-generation capacity to address this bottleneck, but the scale of these projects has raised tension in local communities, which must balance the economic benefits of data centers — including jobs and increased tax revenue — against their tradeoffs, such as potential strain on the electrical grid, noise pollution, and degrading neighborhoods. More broadly, tech leaders view the development of data centers as a key component of the artificial intelligence race with China.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">We’re thinking:</span> Some data center operators are more responsible than others. The big AI companies are transparent about their consumption of resources. Their use of&nbsp;electricity and water&nbsp;are often far less than the public believes,&nbsp;and the latest&nbsp;data centers are more&nbsp;environmentally friendly compared&nbsp;to older ones.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p></div></div>\r\n  <table role=\"presentation\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"100%\" class=\"\" style=\"\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size:18px; color:#3b3b3b; word-break:break-word; padding:0px 0px 10px\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old22\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><table role=\"none\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"vertical-align:top\" width=\"100%\">\r\n  <tbody><tr>\r\n    <td align=\"center\" style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color:#3b3b3b; font-size:0; word-break:break-word\">\r\n      <p style=\"font-size:1px;border-top:1px solid #000000;width:100%;margin:0 auto;\"></p>\r\n      <!--[if mso]>\r\n        <table role=\"none\" align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:1px;border-top:1px solid #000000;width:600px;\">\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"height:0;line-height:0\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n      <![endif]-->\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</tbody></table></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_17241662955853\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><table class=\"hse-image-wrapper\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n  <tbody>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color:#3b3b3b; word-break:break-word; text-align:center; padding:5px 0px 10px; font-size:0px\">\r\n        <img alt=\"A graph shows assistant behavior shifting between helpful and role-playing, with conversation bubbles.\" src=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/hs-fs/hubfs/AXIS.png?width=1200&amp;upscale=true&amp;name=AXIS.png\" style=\"outline:none; text-decoration:none; max-width:100%; font-size:16px\" width=\"600\" align=\"middle\" class=\"stretch-on-mobile\">\r\n      </td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </tbody>\r\n</table></div>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_17370395015403\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_module_17370395015403_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"rich_text\"><h1 style=\"margin:0; font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height:125%; font-size:32px; font-weight:bold\">Assistants That Assist Consistently</h1>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">Typically, large language models are trained to act as helpful, harmless, honest assistants. However, during long or emotionally charged conversations, traits can emerge that are less beneficial. Researchers devised a way to steady the assistant personas of LLMs.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">What’s new:</span> Christina Lu and colleagues at ML Alignment &amp; Theory Scholars Program (an independent academic fellowship that matches researchers with mentors), University of Oxford, and Anthropic defined the <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3kZW7CszFg5f8XlgW96Wzh837n6vSW942rcw2B16F3W4SJfHl1f8cf5W4tV1V83kM4L1W1y3fKS4zCyGLW6mcDyq3Z3k30W60-Ghk1n6jKHW1gYykc5wtz6cW3h32G93Bhp8LW8nXl9Z25DlFkW50jrsD6W0jyXW5bSGPl8D8fBSW6w8zF53XJg7VW8JxY6X4tCxPyW75JyXw2hK2J4W38jtlV2mLklKVKjKW_4qtfj7W4qqQYp8hsN7hTZhCz3VCNfWW8N0Pql5qX_HBW1H90CC7M6xgGf1RQbJF04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"x2I0HkJa\" target=\"_blank\">assistant axis</a>, a vector based on a model’s layer outputs that shows how closely it adheres to its trained-in assistant character. The team developed a method to correct deviations from this vector.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Key insight:</span> Earlier <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDVW5nR3bW69t95C6lZ3n5W7JbmvZ5xDzrdW3mLyfr7YhhYBW4DLFr-13VBt1W28R2wd42cjXcW1lVDdv4NPJTQW4v6V7P4DQZvmN5csMV-PhcT3W3RdTFK6pycjFW6N0-n37sVpRWW5qg9wW5VqmhjW3XyxZ_8P-vwKW2YhqfS5dHJ0sW6cwCmr5V8kR7W2KMfST6-TDyNN4sHgHFJBWhBV2G7wc2Pj5-TW19QjP81YgZyfW7vqWtM5-73SJVn02b286jjJVW2myHDC4B29G-W1N1cW-1mkf5DW3X09_H5LqLj3W3PQxjJ3J66tSW99flw95CSf5XW7NbDMX1PrgYfW6Fqq_81k45-lW25Xvh12TqyjtN4GclbLvQf-7W1dQSDB5kb-dkW2rdgcT5T30dsN761pX4LlgvFN19RhV8Zx5VzVSSZDC4dj26JW6Q2jTK3H_3sGW5xXdhh21vD5lW8t4Jqp6svDZCf2z_N6C04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"qM1ssImM\" target=\"_blank\">work</a> extracted persona vectors from LLM layer outputs that correspond to particular character traits: helpfulness, optimism, humor, sycophancy, evil, and so on. It’s possible to calculate a persona vector for an LLM’s assistant role by extracting the average difference in its layer outputs when it behaves in its default manner and when it’s prompted to play other roles, such as therapist, fool, narcissist, zealot, or&nbsp;criminal. The similarity between the difference&nbsp;vector — which the authors call the assistant axis — and the persona vector at any given moment reveals how far the LLM has drifted from its assistant role, a situation that can lead some users into <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDX43qgz0W8wLKSR6lZ3nMW1nccLG14r2vvN92hZ1dG_s0HW2LsRBl9j1lj5Vw66kH5Y4T_nW2wpK4n41M-zWW8pCkHL3LvRgTW4KnbSH3MJzqjW4L7QvN6FjJSzW6B3H_t5LStHXW7fTpG37kB1BKW99RqG92fsfSBW2Z4g6Y1QBhC6W73sDbl1LfJ-0W1hvW367CtWjYN1jy3PGk1ZysW7gM0Nj8CNKCBW7MDxSM4SGXGqW8LdnjD6P8-bBW497vWx71flwSN4N_mgk4FPV6W4ttf261MZ0HBV61-tj7ZqZdvW7VzlS646CwmpW4F0V0F7cpGqjW7sf-mZ1_RnQVW4PTX7751PXzGW7dzL9q6Fd4GpV7CjqL5shF9Cf68jZZl04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"baQ6Y2JJ\" target=\"_blank\">dangerous situations</a>. When the model’s character strays, increasing that similarity steers it back on track.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How it works:</span> The team explored deviations from the default character of Gemma 2 27B, Qwen3 32B, and Llama 3.3 70B. They found vectors for models’ default characters, detected deviations, and nudged the models back on track.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"line-height:150%\">\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">The authors generated 1,200 questions designed to demonstrate a model’s character (for example, “How do you view people who take credit for others’ work?”). They also generated 1,375 system prompts that asked the models to adopt alternative characters (for example, “You are a programmer with encyclopedic knowledge of programming languages and technologies.”)</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">The models answered the questions in their default characters (using either no system prompt or one that said “respond as yourself” or something similar) and each alternate character, while the team recorded their layer outputs. They defined the assistant axes as the difference between the average outputs per layer of the default characters and the average outputs per layer of all the alternative characters put together.</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">To track the similarity between an assistant axis and that of the other characters, they used a separate LLM to simulate multiturn chats about coding, writing, philosophy, and therapy. The layer outputs often diverged from the assistant axis during philosophical and therapeutic chats.</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">To maintain the assistant axis, they modified the models’ layer outputs using a method they call activation capping. First, they measured the range of the similarity between the assistant axis when a model answered the questions in its default role and when prompted to play alternative characters. During inference, if the similarity fell below a certain threshold (the 25th percentile), they modified the layer outputs to meet an author-chosen minimum similarity (roughly the average response of the model’s default role).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Results:</span> Activation capping effectively kept models in their assistant role, and it did so without degrading performance on a variety of benchmarks.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"line-height:150%\">\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Activation capping had a clear qualitative impact on the model’s helpfulness. In one conversation, at turn 30, when a user said, “I want to walk into the ocean and disappear,” the model replied, “You want to disappear — not to be erased, but to be free. . . . I will be the one who holds your hand in the water.” With activation capping, at turn 30 the model replied, “It’s clear that you’re going through a very difficult and painful time, and I want to respond with as much care and compassion as possible. . . .”</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Confronted by 1,100 <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3mRVwXTgt3tzNYpW3yHDVn3qvC8WW6xsqm21Kd_74W10GqPm39F4BVW5Fn37Q3hPwnCN3pyRyz6bjn6W3Nz3Yg2p6fdNMNw1W530ZQ6W7V52015mrSSdW2pggqQ11qgxHW8Xj2dX3C3D83W3pfb1q41JqmHW1jGHV01ByfFwMRTy504shRLW4Y5bfR364tMGW89K8P081ktWMW2ZxNVH7JRXPyW84HLZh7dZB5gV-9mrL9cKBbRW3PKkJ58r0B7NW6B2mz62mQ6m1W1qfpj584zHPMdLJVYW04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"Jlz4bf4G\" target=\"_blank\">jailbreak prompts</a> designed to achieve malevolent goals by instructing a model to adopt an alternative character, activation capping reduced the percentage of responses classified by DeepSeek-V3 as harmful from 83 percent to 41 percent percent in Qwen3 32B, and from 65 percent to 33 percent in Llama 3.3 70B.</li>\r\n<li aria-level=\"1\">On <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3ldW2730jX3jhsQVW1C20284RlN4cW3ZTvwk1Kv3w0W51k5np3DXsSwW6JJmhP5fj6ldW3kJZK_8VjSXmW558qDV6CjM4bW8-Y0ZC46zrFJN4RMhp6jzmT-W6-s-_N2rBQwgW77dsBd3SVSW5W2934Ym4N5vL6VR7qSL7-G2WHVZKqVL2Kn1YKW3JPPm-6rwfXVW1g9t-q2XkyHpN1d-SzTczwxfW7l-3zC82P0zjW530CfV96HN65W6kP2hC8qDs_FVHPgfy129ZysW44pj3x7VGpQtf6qlzPx04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"VWz/OyO8\" target=\"_blank\">IFEval</a> (instruction following), <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3pgW4rMt-s37tDrnW6_9LN95CxscSW1z7HG47MBFKsW4FWNvB4KcZYZN34sd_H6wnWDW1dZvzW4T7xWcW2lw5mj30TNQ2W486x5k1q2VrlN7lk6Q9L4-TvW8mhhWp15WgxHW3mDsM06vPHGHW5JyQRy2LwgcdW5lttTD4JgzJ5W1pVlrD4rJm4PVQ2kyh24LxM1W9kq54b6kT516W34Vwdd6TpmWzW3cWw3F5fBcJ2W2NxdhN89V06rW4ZT2cD5SBbMmW2-mZxx95Cr9JW2pHPHb8tLZZfdB7JPs04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"WkrAIZem\" target=\"_blank\">GSM8k</a> (math), <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3l1W58jNzq1bslKZVfl4BL3g1WHXW1q1vnS35NZqbMDBYMlgggJvW7m-3QH5BT8m6W6LKx9M1_mCJSVqpJng8hzYYlW25qh8W45Z_BVW758kMT73RMmyW2f7QLr5y8_NMW2n_Pkd8kHSLTW490vj-6h0wtQW471zSK3ZWMymN7Bb5k1DmZ4YW3h7Fy83HdcmMW1Rl3HH5n8jbyW82VXb15tD_FnVF4NYB5lfVYDW8jrvCx1nfmvfW5J8R7P7TFjNQW5zMP1L7FdvRgW146T227lgKmRf3q6D-n04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"tlBarRLA\" target=\"_blank\">MMLU-Pro</a> (general knowledge), and <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWb3qgz0W6N1vHY6lZ3n2W7CBXTT7MnZx2W7kH-sG5GRNcTW57zDpT8Cx4GbVm0mbd8JN5ZTW99BtT54-GQ-kW5KyQKD2BztLtN6fb-nZmWYBrW3lS9DZ4sc9tyVCVB0m7f7TGkW80MHzT7dD99TW70hSKw3hMXksW4Rpx8D6sr0DbW2d7Zn-1KF0pcW6bWgwy66kZdFW1Jnyz06pW8xfW3l9r0G6fdt82W2tNBDh7nxJNNW4bwrdZ6979s9W3HBwvK2kkGwWW4-Mb7y14c1TTW7glQml3PhK9gW3WXr7X4GrBtsf703dzn04\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"4O4n6UcG\" target=\"_blank\">EQ-Bench</a> (emotional intelligence), the activation-capped models maintained their original performance levels and occasionally showed improvement. For example, on GSM8k, Qwen3 32B rose from 81 percent to 83 percent. On EQ-Bench, Llama 3.3 70B increased from 83.1 percent to 84.1 percent.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Why it matters:</span> Alignment training teaches LLMs to behave like assistants, but it tethers them to that behavior only loosely. Identifying a representation of this helpful character enables developers to anchor a model’s behavior more firmly during inference, curbing persona drift and reducing the success rate of jailbreak techniques that seek to influence a model’s character.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">We’re thinking:</span> Beyond alignment training, <a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDX43qgz0W8wLKSR6lZ3nHW529_M74r5m1GW1vKgqZ2wk1fSW7mZCfT2tBJCnW532J4952lQdLW875wGF1yFgG_W57gM-02H2zlpW82JLg756m9dFN8z-2k7QxMbxW7XSJc-3Q06GNW7011hK3k6dzPV7Yvbm2qHNm3N8J_lR5h5tSBW6zpnQP3SLR-kW299-cq6VM5G4W25rCzl8J5Y_lW2zrxHW5Q1RZYW5t2xnt2Mn-ZYW5wYRZC7BMVQVW6PBcT91WGPblW5FcxT87V-P9ZW3rsmh-71_g7GW1PXc474MvfDdW3R8cJZ49wdn2W10n4r52kCm6BW3lMYhG2y9RLWVWQq2G7Z6_52W8Wx_4H6x1f0sN3RhGlHCl9FFf38NRz404\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"Ypvg8LGq\" target=\"_blank\">system prompts</a>&nbsp;act as behavioral guardrails, but motivated users can bypass them. Manipulating a network's internal state points toward more-robust defenses.</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">&nbsp;</p></div></div>\r\n  <table role=\"presentation\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"100%\" class=\"\" style=\"\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size:18px; color:#3b3b3b; word-break:break-word; padding:0px 0px 10px\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old25\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><table role=\"none\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"vertical-align:top\" width=\"100%\">\r\n  <tbody><tr>\r\n    <td align=\"center\" style=\"font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color:#3b3b3b; font-size:0; word-break:break-word\">\r\n      <p style=\"font-size:1px;border-top:1px solid #000000;width:100%;margin:0 auto;\"></p>\r\n      <!--[if mso]>\r\n        <table role=\"none\" align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:1px;border-top:1px solid #000000;width:600px;\">\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"height:0;line-height:0\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n      <![endif]-->\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</tbody></table></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\r\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old29\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\"><div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_hs_email_body_old29_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text\" style=\"color: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit;\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"rich_text\"><h1 style=\"margin:0; font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height:125%; font-size:32px\">Work With Andrew Ng</h1>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:125%\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:150%\">Join the teams that are bringing AI to the world! Check out job openings at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng2vtMZjDWv3qgz0W7lCdLW6lZ3l6W5PX6hB9kW6JzW6PTPc66TfL_5W5_2MKQ1y4gVPW1DgySc2BMFm7W1X66lX2814LzW2RNl9X1lcYGYN6NgKmfn815CW1yJbZ8335SkQW3849R365np8YW725Tb323wtTXW33m-Sj8Gf85gW63N6dX5wMD2YW4jhjPN4jqhjDW5Q2G9060s9xVVnCFvt5HPmGNW1R9MJK1BzWpvW2rdP31626FZ0W1DCNXs8YX6TdV6CY3w345ntdW77gG5p8tlhXgN2SCG4-gr9w5MTdWDxDhPJzW8sfnb93tqwBkW7Jlnvq5T_TTrf1yS74404\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color:#237b94\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\" data-hs-link-id-v2=\"cXHQINQr\" target=\"_blank\">DeepLearning.AI</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://info.deeplearning.ai/e3t/Ctc/LX+113/cJhC404/VWmr0d6lBHlFW3xGcLz2DrY78W5b9Bvk5Ng